Create character arrays like this in your main:
    char word1[] = {'h', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o', '\0'};
    char word2[] = {'w', 'o', 'r', 'l', 'd', '\0'};
//You can't use square brackets
Create a function called worldLength that takes 
a char array as a parameter and 
returns the length of the array.
int worldLength(char *word){
    int counter = 0;
    while(*(word+?) != '\0'){
        ?
    }
    return counter;
}

Use pointer arithmetic to iterate over the array.
When you encounter '\0', finish loop, 
return size to function call.